cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper deals with computer vision applications such as robotics and autonomous driving, which are typically covered under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes an algorithm for moving object detection and depth estimation using stereo cameras, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). The algorithm also involves the use of Kalman filters, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, falling under the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and multi-threading suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
